Hand Recognition System

This project is a computer vision-based hand recognition system that can detect, track, and interpret hand gestures in real-time. 
It enables gesture-based control and human-computer interaction without the need for physical input devices.


ðŸ§  Key Features
Real-time hand detection
Finger & landmark extraction
Gesture recognition (e.g., counting fingers, open/close hand gestures)
Works with webcam or external camera
Easy to integrate with interactive applications (e.g., games, UI control)


ðŸ”§ Technologies Used
Component	Tools Used
Language	Python
Computer Vision	OpenCV
Hand Tracking	MediaPipe / Custom ML model
Environment	Jupyter / Python Script
Version Control	Git & GitHub


ðŸ“Œ How It Works
The webcam captures the hand.
The system detects hand keypoints (landmarks).
The gesture classifier identifies which gesture is being shown.
The output is displayed or used as a control signal.


ðŸŽ¯ Use Cases
Sign language interpretation
Touchless UI control
Robotics & automation control
Gaming and VR interaction systems


